{
  "texts": [
    "We select multiple-choice reading comprehension (MCRC) and sentiment classification as case studies for the analysis.",
    "MCRC requires the correct answer option to be selected based on several inputs element: the context paragraph, the question and the set of answer options.",
    "Multiple-choice (MC) assessments are a widely employed method for evaluating the competencies of candidates across diverse settings and tasks on a global scale (Lai et al., 2017a; Richardson et al., 2013a; Sun et al., 2019; Levesque et al., 2012).",
    "Given their consequential impact on realworld decisions, the selection of appropriate MC questions tailored to specific scenarios is important for content creators.",
    "Consequently, there is a need to comprehend the underlying factors that contribute to the complexity of these assessments."
  ]
}